found Miſs C at home I 21 st . June Monday
slept more than I had done for since Thursday
s letter to G . House . June 22
r their Majesties for 3 or 4 days
set out wth Mr & Mrs. Vesey for Richmond Hill -- it was a rainy day
comes once or twice a Week
sent my letter by this Post to Lady Wake , & one to my friend Miſs Litchfield wth . some of my diary . June 24
Thursday -- recd . & answer 'd notes to Miſs Agill & Miſs Gunning -- had ye . Shoemaker & c . Miſs Bloſset paid
were gone for a few days
Thursday or late on Wedy . Eveg . -- I wrote
had heard they were much frighten 'd abt . 10 days ago
Yesterday -- Remarks on ye . french & English Ladies by Andrews -- I do not much like ye . Author 's
were not let in -- in ye . Morning Sunday
was brought to bed last Monday
found a Note from Lady Stormont Tuesday
12 years old who is at West Minster School came
sent that & Mr. D 's by this nights
many years -- her Husband was a Gentleman of la r ge fortune s
20 years of age -- handsome & very amiable -- ye . 2 d . 16 -- ye . 3 d . 14 all 3 were charming
died in America during ye . last War -- She has now
saw her son William who is a clever boy -- he was 14 Yesterday
Sat up till 12 Began a letter to Lady Wake Saturday
spoke in ye . house of commons yesterday
complimented Coll . Cathcart on his succeſs Yesterday
went to bed abt . 12 o'Clock Sunday
July 1784 Went to day with Mrs .. & Miſs Ord Master Bigg & Mr. Pepys -- to Mr. Agar 's
made my peace wth . them for not having been ye . whole Winter
walk 'd home at 11 ye . Moon shone bright & it was a real Summers Eveg . Monday
July 1784 . Lord Dartrey call 'd early , brought
inform 'd me he should be in Derbyshire this Summer
next Week . I was so fatigued wth . ye . heat I had not ye power of doing any thing but conversed
Saturday to Thames Ditton , he sent
ye . Glovers had call 'd Recd . a kind friendly letter from Mrs. Alison in reply to my congratulations upon her Marriage Thursday
July 1784 -- Recd . a Note from Lady Clavering wch . inform
Sunday & c & c & c . My Uncle Frederick came
murder 'd by the orders of ye . Czar . as this is now
had not seen him these 3 years
brought Mrs. V . & me home ½ past 12 oClock Tuesday
wrote an answer to Miſs Clarkes to be ready for tomorrows Post . Wednesday
Saturday & then Mr. Stanhope & I set out
had requested me in her letter of Yesterday
days Post . Mr .. D—— Sen . came
did not go in . Mrs. Handcock had call 'd yesterday
Friday Morng . Left Mr. Dewes at 1 : call 'd
went to Buxton where is to be next Monday
